<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861219-0042 </DOCNO><HL> Martin Marietta WinsArmy Helicopter JobFor $365.2 Million</HL><DD> 12/19/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ML GLD MOTAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Martin Marietta Corp. said it received a $365.2 million contract to produce targeting and night-vision equipment for the Army's Apache helicopters.    Williams Steel Industries Inc. won a $24.6 million Air Force contract for aircraft noise-suppression equipment.    Gould Inc. received a $17.3 million Navy contract for anti-submarine warfare equipment for cruisers, destroyers and frigates.    Motorola Inc. was issued a $12.7 million Navy contract for Phoenix missile equipment. </TEXT></DOC>